note: Accepting your _decode_value() change. Added an explicit self.disk_cache.expire() lazy-purge call on the miss path when ttl is configured — task spec requires this to actually evict/trim expired records from disk (checking 'key in self.disk_cache' alone leaves expired entries on disk, just treats them as absent). Guarded by self.ttl is not None so it's a no-op when TTL unused.

